updated:"2019-06-22T22:45:22-07:00",url:"http://www.fecklessthug.com/2019/06/us-humans.html",selfLink:"https://www.googleapis.com/blogger/v3/blogs/9198389381789324893/posts/7782091938936151820",title:"Us Humans",content:"&quot;But there are no bacteria in Mars, and directly these invaders arrived, \r<br>directly they drank and fed, our microscopic allies began to work their \r<br>overthrow. Already when I watched them they were irrevocably doomed, \r<br>dying and rotting even as they went to and fro. It was inevitable. By \r<br>the toll of a billion deaths man has bought his birthright of the earth, \r<br>and it is his against all comers; it would still be his were the \r<br>Martians ten times as mighty as they are. For neither do men live nor \r<br>die in vain.&quot; -- Herbert George Wells",
