published:"2008-11-03T21:47:00-08:00",updated:"2020-06-05T19:10:02-07:00",url:"http://www.fecklessthug.com/2008/11/hartsfields-landing.html",selfLink:"https://www.googleapis.com/blogger/v3/blogs/9198389381789324893/posts/8613653629547209450",title:"hartsfield's landing",content:'<blockquote>\nTown Clerk Rick Erwin says the northern<br />\nNew Hampshire town is proud of its tradition, but says,<br />\n"the most important thing is that we exemplify a 100 percent vote."<br />\n<a href="http://www.seacoastonline.com/articles/20081103-NEWS-81104001" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">http://www.seacoastonline.com/articles/20081103-NEWS-81104001</a><br />\n<br />\n"What I can\'t stomach are people who\'re<br />\nout to convince people that the educated<br />\nare soft and privileged and out to make<br />\nthem feel like they\'re less, then, you know,<br />\nhe may be educated, but I\'m plain-spoken, just like you."<br />\n<span style="font-family: &quot;trebuchet ms&quot;; font-size: 85%;">- aaron sorkin, "hartsfield\'s landing"</span><br />\n\n<br /></blockquote>\n',
