published:"2008-09-16T06:23:00-07:00",updated:"2019-04-18T01:24:30-07:00",url:"http://www.fecklessthug.com/2008/09/potential.html",selfLink:"https://www.googleapis.com/blogger/v3/blogs/9198389381789324893/posts/7870784996110976323",title:"potential",content:'lately i\'ve been absorbed listening to<br />\nchristopher hitchens and richard feynman;<br />\nrecently i happened upon "god said ha" --<br />\ndidn\'t know about "letting go of god"<br />\ntill just this now.<br />\n<br />\ni sometimes call this curiosity.<br />\n<br />\npolitics lends itself to self-serving acts.<br />\nbut at some point the world needs better --<br />\ni wonder about potential -- not feymanesque<br />\npotential-energy but the potential of what a<br />\nperson has learned, how they think, and what<br />\nthey can do to move society forward.<br />\n<br />\npalin has mass appeal with seemingly zero<br />\ngravity of thought; mccain has the height<br />\nand stature of a hero but seems to have<br />\nlittle mass appeal; so i calculate their<br />\npotential as approaching zero.<br />\n<br />\ni\'d ask god to help us when they get elected<br />\nbut christopher hitchens -- and now i suspect<br />\n<a href="http://juliasweeney.blogspot.com/2008/09/thanks-for-all-notes.html">julia sweeney</a> -- would scold me.',
